File: South Africans have grown used to frequent power outages. eNCA/Athi Mtongana JOHANNESBURG - You can finally prepare your Sunday lunch without worrying about electricity. Eskom has suspended power cuts, if only for a few hours. The embattled utility will implement Stage 2 power cuts from 4pm. WATCH: Govt at coalface of power crisis Eskom says this is due to an improvement in available generation capacity. It says it will publish further updates if any changes occur. It's once again calling on the public to use electricity sparingly.